     <h1>We have a campus you must visit to appreciate</h1> 
     <p>Located in scenic Santa Barbara, California with mountain and ocean views, Westmont is one of the most beautiful campuses in the world. The college decision-making process must include a visit to the campus of your choice.</p> 
     <p>Colleges and universities have as distinct a personality as you do. The very best way to experience what life is like on a college campus is to visit and see for yourself.</p> 
     <p>You can begin visiting college campuses any time during the process, but the best time to visit is when the campus is in “full swing.” If you are a junior or senior, you should explore the campus during the week when classes are meeting, students are studying, and ordinary day-to-day activities are taking place. This means visiting during the school week.</p> 
     <p>We welcome you to visit our beautiful campus to experience how Westmont can prepare you for a lifelong journey of spiritual growth, academic excellence, and personal maturity–all within a spectacular setting.</p> 
     <p>Campus tours are conducted from 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. weekdays and from 9:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m. on most Saturdays when the College is in session. Tours are also available Monday through Friday throughout the summer. Schedule your visit today by calling 1-(800)-777-9011, or completing our online visit request form:</p> 
     <p><a href="http://webapps.westmont.edu/forms/admissions/visit_new/">Visit Request Form</a></p> 
     <h3>Things you need to know prior to your visit.</h3> 
     <ul> 
      <li>For directions to campus: <a href="directions_to_campus.html">Directions</a> </li> 
      <li>Once you arrive on campus, visit our admission office on the first floor of Kerrwood Hall. For a map of campus: <a href="http://www.westmont.edu/_visitors/pdf/map.pdf">Campus Map</a> </li> 
      <li>For all overnight visits you will need to bring a sleeping bag, pillow, towel, and other personal items.</li> 
      <li>We are unable to offer overnight accommodations for parents and siblings. For local accommodations please consult our Hotel Accommodations Guide: <a href="santa-barbara-lodging.html">Local Hotels</a> </li> 
      <li>Overnight stay with students (must be scheduled at least two weeks in advance)</li> 
     </ul> 
     <h3>Make the most of your visit…</h3> 
     <ul> 
      <li>Sit in on classes and talk with Westmont professors</li> 
      <li>Ideal overnight visits should begin on Sun., Tues., or Thurs. in order to attend chapel, which is held Mon., Wed. and Fri., from 10:30a.m. to 11:20a.m. Or, arrive by 9:00 a.m. the day of chapel.</li> 
      <li>Meet with your Admission Counselor</li> 
      <li>Tour our excellent science labs and comfortable residence halls.</li> 
     </ul> 
